description:
Binary: Scrape recipe from URL using Tandoor API.

Input: {"tandoor": {...}, "url": "https://..."}
Output: {"success": bool, "recipe_json": {...}, "images": [...]}

Uses TandoorClient::scrape_recipe_from_url() already in src/tandoor/client.rs.
Pattern: See src/bin/tandoor_test_connection.rs for binary template.

Binary: Combined scrape + create operation.

Input: {"tandoor": {...}, "url": "...", "additional_keywords": [...]}
Output: {"success": bool, "recipe_id": N, "name": "...", "source_url": "..."}

Uses TandoorClient::import_recipe_from_url() already in src/tandoor/client.rs.

Get single food diary entry from FatSecret API.

Input:
{
  "params": {
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "entry_id": "integer"
  }
}

Output:
{
  "data": {
    "entry": { ...diary_entry_fields... }
  }
}

Requirements:
- < 500ms cold start
- Pagination support (if listing)
- Error handling for not found

Location: src/lambdas/fatsecret/diary_get_entry.rs

Search FatSecret food database by name/brand.

Input:
{
  "params": {
    "query": "string",
    "max_results": 50,
    "page_number": 1
  }
}

Output:
{
  "data": {
    "foods": [ ... ],
    "pagination": {
      "total_results": 1234,
      "page": 1,
      "has_more": true
    }
  }
}

Requirements:
- Full-text search support
- Brand filtering
- Pagination support
- < 300ms cold start (read-heavy)
- Result caching

Location: src/lambdas/fatsecret/foods_search.rs

Create food diary entry in FatSecret API.

Input:
{
  "params": {
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "meal_type": "Breakfast|Lunch|Dinner|Other",
    "food_entries": [
      { "food_id": 123, "serving": 1.5, "unit": "cup" },
      ...
    ]
  }
}

Output:
{
  "data": {
    "entry_id": 123,
    "entry": { ... }
  }
}

Requirements:
- Batch food entry support
- Validation of meal_type
- Nutrition calculation validation
- < 500ms cold start

Location: src/lambdas/fatsecret/diary_create_entry.rs

Binary: Create recipe in Tandoor from scraped/provided data.

Input: {"tandoor": {...}, "recipe": {...}, "additional_keywords": [...]}
Output: {"success": bool, "recipe_id": N, "name": "..."}

Uses TandoorClient::create_recipe() already in src/tandoor/client.rs.
